      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APPLAUDING (10) worked from a wide barrier but was too good at this circuit and distance last week, getting home by 3.4 metres. Draws on the back row this time but is capable of winning again if she gets the gaps. TIZZY LIZZIE (5) produced a good performance last week when she raced parked but stuck on for third at this circuit and distance, beaten 4.2 metres. That was her fourth placing in five starts since a win from a  similar barrier here. Major player. FOREVER ONTHE PUNT (6) has been good from this barrier in his last two attempts at this circuit and distance, missing by a neck two back before leading and digging deep to score last time. Go well again. LITTLE SASSY BOY (9) has been close-up in two starts here since a Young win, missing by a nose last week. Draws for a trail and has upside.",
